Generic single-database configuration.

Migration Strategy (V12 15.2)
=============================
- SQLite  : database.py auto-migrations are canonical. Do NOT use Alembic for SQLite.
- PostgreSQL: Alembic migrations (this directory) are canonical. Run `alembic upgrade head`.

When adding new columns or tables:
  1. Update db/models.py with the new schema.
  2. For SQLite users: database.py create_tables() handles schema changes automatically.
  3. For PostgreSQL users: generate an Alembic revision with `alembic revision --autogenerate`
     and commit it to this directory.